        "$:/plugins/.mr/slider/readme": {
            "created": "20181101134242465",
            "creator": "Mohammad",
            "text": "!! What ia slider?\nSlider is a small plugin to create connected contents like step by step tutorial or guided help, lessons and similar.\n\n!! Parts of slider\nEach slider has three main parts\n\n# Slider tiddler\n# Sliders contents (a set of tiddlers also called ''slides'')\n# Slider footer\n\n!! Slider tiddler\nThe slider tiddler is a tiddler tagged with `slider` and has \n\n* A header contains the slider details (like caption, tag, number of slides)\n* A slide list panel, to show the list of slides (e.g tiddlers) in the slider and let to add new slides by drag and drop and  re-order the slides in the slider\n* A footer, which is a tiddler contains one line text to be shown as a footer at the bottom of each slide\n\n!! Slides\nSlides (tiddlers) can be added to a specified slider in several ways including\n\n# By clicking on the `New slide` button on the slider manager tiddler\n# By dragging and droping a tiddler from sidebar into the `List of slides` on the slider manager tiddler\n# By opening the `sidebar / Slider Manager` tab and then clicking on the `Add slide to ...` button\n# By creating new tiddler and tagging with the specified slider title\n# By tagging an exisiting tiddler with the specified slider title\n\n!! Navigate among slides\n# Set the desired slider as the active slider by opening it (e.g. from sidebar) and clicking on `Set for presentation`\n# From the //List of slides// click on the first slide\n# One the footer of newly opened slide, click on the next button to navigate to the next slide\n# You can click on the slide-list button to open a local window and see the list of all slides, then you can click on any slide you like and jump to that slide\n# The slide footer also has a //previous// button which lets to navigate to previous slide in the list\n\n@@color:white;background:black;width:60%;margin:25px;padding:15px;\n''Note:'' Using //zoomin story// view may be more convenient when you use slider and navigate through slides. This is becuase, one tiddler is open at a time\n@@\n\n!! Slide footer\n* The slider footer can be used to add a text to all slides in a slider.\n* The slider footer is a tiddler and can be opned and edited\n* The slider footer has the same title of slider with `-Footer` prefix and tagged with `slideFooter`\n* The footer can be used for date stamp, author and institution name or any other information you like.\n* The footer can be formatted for color, size, font and etc. It can accept all the standard markup.\n\n@@color:white;background:black;width:50%;margin:25px;padding:15px;\n''Note:'' The footer is designed to be a single line. Use it for semantic purpose and try to keep it consistent.\n@@\n\n!! Colorify slides\nTo apply css classes to slides and colorify them\n\n* Fill in the `class` field of desired tiddler with a custom class\n* The slider has several classes ready to use like (~MistyRose, Bisque, Honeydew, ...)\n* For all available colors see $:/plugins/.mr/slider/stylesheet/slide-background-class\n\n!!! How use your own class\n<<<\n* Develop your classes inside a tiddler tagged with `$:/tags/Stylesheet`\n* \"\"\"This is a sample class\n `.mycls{color:white; background-color:#eee;}`\n\"\"\"\n<<<\n\n!! Slider theme\nThere is two different themes for slider manager and slider tiddler\n\n* Light theme\n* Dark theme\n\nTo change the slider theme, from sidebar open `Slider Manager` and click on theme button to choose the light or dark slider theme.\n\n!! Slide view mode\nThere is two view mode for slider\n\n* A ''normal slide view mode'' (tiddler in normal height and any story view mode)\n* A ''single slide view mode'' (tiddlers fill whole the screen height and use of `zoomin` story view)\n\nTo change the view mode, open the `Slider Manager` from sidebar and click on `Single slide view/Normal slide view` button\n\n!! Installation\nSimply drag and drop the below ling into your wiki\n* $:/plugins/.mr/slider",
            "title": "$:/plugins/.mr/slider/readme",
            "tags": "",
            "modifier": "Mohammad",
